  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This package documents a V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The computational model has been applied in clinical research settings to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for centrifugal blood pump designs used under cardiopulmonary bypass conditions. A full 13-factor assessment was conducted at Model Risk Level 2 for a Class II device; seven factors were formally assessed and six were scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2. All assessed factors met or exceeded required credibility levels, and the overall assessment outcome is Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-cbp-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-cbp-piv-flowfield"
  ],
